Ivory Coast to Plant 300,000 Hectares With Rubber, AIP Reports

-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-09-21T11:45:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/ivory-coast-to-plant-300-000-hectares-with-rubber-aip-reports.html
Ivory Coast  plans to plant as much
as 300,000 hectares (741,320 acres) with rubber trees by 2020,
Agence de Presse Ivoirienne reported, citing Kouadio Dian, an
official at the countryâ€™s Rubber Development Fund.  The West African nation plans to boost rubber output to
600,000 metric tons a year by 2020, the Abidjan-based  news
agency  said. Ivory Coast produced 231,500 tons last year and
aims to produce 244,500 tons in 2011, the Ministry of Finance
said on Sept. 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
